{
  "texts": [
    "All future turns are thus implicitly \"compressed\" into Q π, eliminating the need for any explicit handling of multi-turn trajectories.",
    "Right: Iterating this procedure (π ← π ′) yields multi-turn improvements using only single-turn RLHF tools.",
    "Since we proceed in a series of online batches, we refer to this as \"batch online.\"",
    "This paper is organized as follows.",
    "We formulate the outcome-driven problem in Section 2 and show the reduction from multi-turn to single-turn RL using our Iterative PPO approach in Section 3."
  ]
}